The paper discusses the equivalence between fully connected layer and convolutional layer in neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories.
